"Preventive Imprisonment"

- is a temporary confinement in jail or prison while undergoing investigation or trial or awaiting final judgment;

w.

"Prison"

- any correctional facility managed by the BUCOR to safekeep and rehabilitate a prisoner convicted by the final judgment, whose sentence exceeds three (3) years, or who is sentenced to serve (2) or more prison terms and whose aggregated sentences exceed three (3) years;

